{
  "card_id": "continuation_pattern",
  "type": "merged_concept",
  "canonical_term": "Continuation Pattern",
  "aliases": [
    "continuation",
    "延续形态"
  ],
  "school": "ICT",
  "definition": "A price sequence that resumes the prevailing trend after a retracement or consolidation, characterized by a rapid V-shaped reversal where the closing price crosses a series of opposite-direction candles within 1-3 bars, breaking out of a consolidation range, fair value gap, or prior swing point to confirm trend continuation.",
  "identification_rules": [
    "Price is in a clear uptrend or downtrend before the pattern forms.",
    "After a consolidation or range, price closes beyond the upper/lower boundary of that range.",
    "Price reaches a fair value gap (FVG) or sweeps a swing low/high, then forms a rapid V-shaped reversal.",
    "Closing price crosses a series of opposite-direction candles (e.g., in an uptrend, closes above the closes of bearish candles) and completes within 1-3 candles; exceeding this range indicates consolidation, not continuation.",
    "A series of same-direction closing candles (multiple bullish or bearish closes) confirms trend continuation.",
    "On a lower timeframe (e.g., 1-hour), a clear closing sequence breakout aligns with the higher timeframe bias (e.g., daily).",
    "Ideally, the continuation pattern does not sweep a short-term high or low simultaneously.",
    "The continuation forms without having reached a higher timeframe target.",
    "Price begins to consolidate with converging trendlines, forming a wedge or triangle shape.",
    "The pattern typically shows decreasing price range over time.",
    "A breakout from the pattern occurs in the direction of the prior trend, confirming the pattern."
  ],
  "trading_implication": "Continuation patterns offer high-probability trend-following entries. For ICT, enter on multi-timeframe alignment (weekly bias + daily swing + hourly entry) with a rapid V-shaped reversal through key levels. For price action, combine with other technical factors and place targets based on pattern height. Avoid three failure scenarios: consolidation instead of continuation, simultaneous sweep of short-term highs/lows, and higher timeframe target already reached.",
  "common_mistakes": [
    "Entering before the continuation pattern fully forms, leading to false breakouts or stop runs.",
    "Ignoring multi-timeframe alignment; trading continuation on a lower timeframe without higher timeframe confirmation.",
    "Mistaking a single reversal candle for a continuation pattern; waiting for closing sequence confirmation.",
    "Setting stops too wide after the pattern forms, resulting in poor risk-reward.",
    "Confusing consolidation with continuation—consolidation lacks rapid V-shaped reversal and often sweeps the opposite side of the range.",
    "Trading continuation when short-term highs/lows are swept simultaneously, risking a new reversal phase.",
    "Chasing continuation after higher timeframe targets are already reached (FOMO).",
    "Being too lenient on the crossing time—if it takes more than 3 candles to cross, it is consolidation, not continuation.",
    "Failing to recognize whether the continuation truly protects a prior swing point (Protected Swing)."
  ],
